                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/898</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-12T11:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of January 4, 5 p.m. No answer having been received to my inquiry I
                    called upon the Minister for Foreign Affairs this morning who said that delay
                    was due to investigation of Minister of Hacienda and that answer would be
                    delivered this afternoon. When received I will report at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
